    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ahtlatl of turquoise (in mosaic or color) in posclassic central Mexico. Also known as a xiuhcoatl. This device used to amplify the propulsive force of spears or darts, in hunting as in warfare, is associated mainly with Xiuhteuctli, but also with Huitzilopochtli and Tezcatlipoca.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
